  "text": "GCNs were first proposed in [CITATION_1] ) where graph convolutional operations were defined in the Fourier domain. The eigendecomposition of the graph Laplacian caused intense computation. Later, smooth parametric spectral filters [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] were introduced to achieve localization in the spatial domain and improve computational efficiency. Recently, [CITATION_4] simplified these spectral methods by a first-order approximation with the Chebyshev polynomials. The spatial graph convolution approaches (Hamilton, Ying, and Leskovec 2017a) define convolutions directly on graph, which sum up node features over all spatial neighbors using adjacency matrix.",
